So, just joking, we started scavenging the big sea of junk of Internet.
And we found a lot of jewels, scattered amongst forgotten torrents and streaming sites... We really felt like Indiana Jones after the discovery of some lost treasure.
So now you have it: a collection of more or less 140 albums which represent a fair sample of that unrepeteable moment that was in the 70s the Progressive Rock renaissance in Italy. Obscure groups, who often published an album only, but the musical level is really high. 
Using the excellent progarchives.com site as a reference map, we recovered archaelogic witness that our country, that now lies under a deep layer of shit, had a glorious artistic past... 
Nowadays we live under the shit, but we have developed excellent apnea techniques to survive :)
And if we had such a past, we hope that in our forgotten culture there is the seed of a better future... 

